<topic id="customizing_js">
  <title>Customizing Web Author Using JavaScript Code</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Customizing Web Author using JavaScript</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>To extend the client-side functionality provided by <ph keyref="webappProduct"/>, you can use
      the <xref keyref="jscript_api">JavaScript API</xref>. To load your JavaScript customization
      code, use one of the following methods:<ul>
        <li>Create a file called <filepath>plugin.js</filepath> and copy it in the
            <filepath>app</filepath> folder of the <ph keyref="webappProduct"/> deployment. </li>
        <li><xref
            href="customizing_plugins.dita#customizing_plugins/webapp_bundle_js_files_in_plugin"
            >Bundle JavaScript code with a Java <term>plugin</term>.</xref></li>
        <li>Bundle the JavaScript code with a <xref
            href="customizing_frameworks.dita#customizing_frameworks"><term>framework</term></xref>.
          Save your code in the <filepath>framework.js</filepath> file (located in the
            <filepath>web</filepath> folder inside the particular <term>framework</term>
          folder).</li>
      </ul></p>
  </body>
